cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL

The paper presents a Python package for selecting representative subsets from large data sets using submodular optimization, which is a common technique in machine learning and data science. The paper also demonstrates the use of subset selection by training machine learning models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
